The paper deals with the problem of matrix completion, which involves reconstructing a matrix from a subset of its entries. This problem is related to compressed sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes a new algorithm for matrix completion that is more efficient than previous methods, which suggests it could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). The algorithm involves randomized sampling and optimization, which are techniques used in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and signal processing (cs.SI).
